{"word":"bien","priority":"★★★","meanings":[{"part_of_speech":"adverb","definition":"よく、上手に、うまく","english_definition":"well, properly, skillfully","examples":[{"sentence":"Il parle bien français.","translation":"彼はフランス語を上手に話します。"},{"sentence":"Elle chante bien.","translation":"彼女は歌がうまい。"},{"sentence":"Tout va bien.","translation":"万事順調だ。"}],"collocations":["bien faire (うまくやる)","bien parler (上手に話す)","bien chanter (上手に歌う)","tout va bien (万事順調)"],"synonyms":["correctement","convenablement","adroitement"],"antonyms":["mal"]},{"part_of_speech":"adverb","definition":"とても、非常に","english_definition":"very, quite, really","examples":[{"sentence":"Il est bien grand.","translation":"彼はとても背が高い。"},{"sentence":"C'est bien gentil de votre part.","translation":"ご親切にどうもありがとうございます。"}],"collocations":["bien grand (とても大きい)","bien gentil (とても親切)"],"synonyms":["très","vraiment","beaucoup"],"antonyms":["peu"]},{"part_of_speech":"noun","definition":"善、良いこと","english_definition":"good, what is good","examples":[{"sentence":"Faire le bien.","translation":"善を行う。"},{"sentence":"Le bien et le mal.","translation":"善と悪。"}],"collocations":["faire le bien (善を行う)","le bien et le mal (善と悪)"],"synonyms":["le bon","le juste"],"antonyms":["le mal"]},{"part_of_speech":"noun","definition":"財産、資産","english_definition":"property, asset, goods","examples":[{"sentence":"Il a beaucoup de biens.","translation":"彼はたくさんの財産を持っている。"},{"sentence":"Les biens immobiliers.","translation":"不動産。"}],"collocations":["biens immobiliers (不動産)","biens meubles (動産)"],"synonyms":["propriété","richesse","fortune"],"antonyms":["dette"]},{"part_of_speech":"interjection","definition":"よし、わかった、承知した","english_definition":"okay, all right, agreed","examples":[{"sentence":"Bien, on y va.","translation":"よし、行こう。"},{"sentence":"Bien, je comprends.","translation":"わかった、理解しました。"}],"collocations":["Bien! (よし！)"],"synonyms":["d'accord","ok","entendu"],"antonyms":[]}],"etymology":{"value":"ラテン語の「bene」（よく）に由来。","priority":"★★☆"},"pronunciation":{"ipa":"/bjɛ̃/","syllables":"1"},"inflection":{"notes":"不変（性数による変化なし）"},"usage_notes":{"explanation":"「bien」は非常に一般的なフランス語の単語で、文脈によって意味が大きく異なります。副詞としては「よく」「とても」の意味があり、名詞としては「善」「財産」の意味があります。また、間投詞としては肯定や同意を表します。","priority":"★★★"},"common_mistakes":{"examples":[{"incorrect":"Je suis bien. (幸福な意味で)","correct":"Je vais bien.","note":"幸福な状態を表現する場合は「Je suis heureux/heureuse.」を使い、「Je vais bien.」は体調や状況が良好な場合に使う。"},{"incorrect":"Il parle français bon.","correct":"Il parle bien français.","note":"副詞は動詞の後に置くのが一般的。"}],"priority":"★★☆"},"related_words":{"derivatives":["bientôt (すぐに)","bienséance (礼儀)","bienvenue (歓迎)","bientot (すぐに)"],"idioms_phrases":["tant bien que mal (なんとか)","c'est bien fait pour lui (それは彼にとって当然の報いだ)"],"priority":"★★★"},"level_frequency":{"CEFR":"A1","frequency_google_ngram":"非常に高頻度","priority":"★☆☆"},"readability_explanation":{"level":"A1","text":"「bien」はフランス語でとてもよく使う言葉です。「元気ですか？」と聞かれたら「Ça va bien, merci.（元気です、ありがとう）」と答えます。また、「C'est bien.（良いね）」のように、何かを褒めるときにも使います。他にも、「上手に」とか「とても」という意味もあります。"},"example_sentences":[{"sentence":"Elle danse très bien.","translation":"彼女はとても上手に踊る。","type":"adverb","meaning_category":"よく、上手に"},{"sentence":"Je vais bien, merci.","translation":"元気です、ありがとう。","type":"adverb","meaning_category":"よく、上手に"},{"sentence":"C'est bien!","translation":"良いね！","type":"interjection","meaning_category":"よし、わかった"},{"sentence":"Il est bien tard.","translation":"もうとても遅い。","type":"adverb","meaning_category":"とても、非常に"},{"sentence":"Il faut faire le bien.","translation":"善を行うべきだ。","type":"noun","meaning_category":"善、良いこと"},{"sentence":"Il a investi dans des biens immobiliers.","translation":"彼は不動産に投資した。","type":"noun","meaning_category":"財産、資産"}]}